---
title: Beef Chiles Rellenos with Poblano Peppers and Chipotle Sauce
description: This recipe is all filler, but we mean that in the best possible way. Soft-roasted poblanos are stuffed to the brim with a warmly spiced mix of ground beef and rice, then blanketed with a rich tomato sauce and a layer of melted Monterrey Jack cheese. In other words, it’s got plenty of substance and south-of-the-border style, too.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/5b76dd3530006c036e19cbf2-0488d579.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/beef-chiles-rellenos-5b76dd3530006c036e19cbf2-e096a571.pdf
author: HelloFresh
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/beef-chiles-rellenos-5b76dd3530006c036e19cbf2
course: main course
time required: 35 minutes
servings: 2
cuisine: Mexican
nutrition:
  calories: 760 kcal
  fat: 37 g
  saturated fat: 15 g
  carbohydrates: 70 g
  sugar: 8 g
  protein: 37 g
  fiber: 6 g
  sodium: 890 mg
---

Wash and dry all produce. Adjust rack to middle position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Bring @water{3/4%cup} and @veggie stock concentrate{1} to a boil in a #small pot{}. Halve @poblano pepper{2} lengthwise; remove cores. Rub with a drizzle of @vegetable oil{}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Roast on a #baking sheet{} until soft, about ~{20%minutes}.

Once stock boils, add @jasmine rice{1/2%cup} to #pot{}. Cover, lower heat, and reduce to a gentle simmer. Cook until tender, about ~{15%minutes}. Meanwhile, halve, peel, and dice @yellow onion{1}. Finely chop @jalapeño{1}(removing ribs and seeds for less heat).

Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{} in a #large pan{} over medium heat. Add jalapeño (to taste) and onion. Cook, tossing, until soft, ~{4-5%minutes}. Add @southwest spice blend{2%tsp} (we sent more) and @ground beef{10%ounce}, breaking up meat. Cook, tossing, until no longer pink, ~{4-5%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Remove from heat.

In another #small pot{}, stir together half the @crushed tomatoes{6.88%ounce} (we sent more than needed), remaining @veggie stock concentrate{1}, @water{1/3%cup}, remaining southwest spice blend, and as much @chipotle powder{1%tsp} as you like (start with a pinch and add more from there). Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Place over medium-low heat and bring to a gentle simmer.

Once rice is done cooking, add to #pan{} with filling. Toss to combine. Season with @salt{}, @pepper{}, and any remaining chipotle powder, if desired. Stuff poblanos with as much filling as will fit. Place in same pan, nestling in remaining unused filling.

> TIP: If your pan is not ovenproof, transfer mixture to a small #baking dish{} at this point.

Drizzle sauce over stuffed poblanos. Sprinkle with @monterey jack cheese{1/2%cup}. Bake in oven until cheese melts, ~{2-3%minutes}. Divide stuffed poblanos and filling from pan between plates and serve.